In a speech at the East Room, President Biden discussed his administration's efforts to address healthcare issues and protect consumers from hidden fees. He emphasized the importance of fairness and not being taken advantage of. The President announced new rules to crack down on junk fees in health insurance plans and close loopholes that allow surprise medical bills. He also highlighted the progress made in lowering prescription drug prices for seniors and people with disabilities through Medicare negotiation. President Biden expressed his commitment to standing up to Big Pharma and defending the Affordable Care Act. He concluded by urging unity and optimism for the future of the country.